<DOC><DOCNO> AP881114-0246 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-11-14-88 2014EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f AM-IBM-Networks     11-14 0112</FIRST><SECOND>AM-IBM-Networks,0117</SECOND><HEAD>IBM Announces Faster Network Products</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   International Business Machines Corp. on Mondayannounced products that allow a network to handle 16 million bits ofinformation per second, four times the previous speed.   IBM said the improvements in its Token-Ring network, whichcompetes with the industry-standard Ethernet and Digital EquipmentCorp.'s Decnet, ``gives customers the increased speed andperformance they need to engage in advanced graphics, image andengineering and scientific applications.''   The Token-Ring network can be used to link computers of allsizes. The enhancements include a special signal converter chip thatdoes the work of six other chips and is made with state-of-the-artfabrication technology.</TEXT></DOC>